rComments: Prof. Turino seems like a very nice man. He is very interested in what he teaches, which is cool. Unfortunately, do not expect to succeed in this class if you are not a music major. The class is "designed for non-music majors" but that's rubbish. The content of this course was highly uninteresting to me and there is a lot of reading to be done.
hard as hell for people not music majors
Quite concerned with culture and voodoo spirits of African music.  Beware all exams are essay format, with little multiple choice.
Awesome guy to hang out with good teacher but watch out for unfair TA's!
